replies.body:
idk if im replying too much but also the "biting" tactic you could express your ways/thoughts
of how you do it

(my way is that if someone is same armor status as me or around the range of it in terms of
melee damage, usually i'd let them get as close as possible to me and try to make them
get thrown off, like if they get to close to think that ill bow, 75% of the time they would try
to bow down a couple shots and thats where i catch them off guard, or if its like a bridging
situation, i dont shoot until they are able to be within the very middle or near end of my side where i can bow them down off the bridge or bow them down w/ 2 to 3 shots, or even let them 95% finish their
bridging and take them down and use their bridge as a chase)
